def: A Hebrew name for God, usually translated in the Old Testamentby the word "Lord".
Contrived for the purpose of making a show, or gainingapplause; deceptive; unreal.
To unfold; to undo; to ravel, as what has been woven.
A decision or rule of a judge or a court, especially an oraldecision, as in excluding evidence.
A hydrocarbon, C6H10, of the acetylene series, obtainedartificially as a colorless, volatile, pungent liquid; -- called alsohexoylene.
A small eminence of a conical form, of land or of ice; a knoll;a hillock. See Hummock. Bartram.
The operation of breaking a bone in order to correct deformity.
An ancient instrument resembling the harp.

The doctrine of those who deny a supernatural agency in themiracles and revelations recorded in the Bible, and in spiritualinfluences; also, any system of philosophy which refers the phenomenaof nature to a blind force or forces acting necessarily or accordingto fixed laws, excluding origination or direction by one intelligentwill.
